     VISN1 Home                       VA Lowell CBOC

   Photo of Lowell clinic VA Lowell CBOC
                                    130 Marshall Road
                                    Lowell, MA 01851
                                  Phone: (978) 671-9000
                                   Fax: (978) 671-9149

                                     Practice Hours:
                                8:00am - 4:30pm, Mon-Fri

                            Directions

      The clinic is located approximately 30 miles northwest of Boston in the
      heart of the Merrimac Valley. The present facility is a pleasant,
   modern, one-story building located 1.5 miles from downtown Lowell. The
    clinic was built in 1992 and was occupied in the Spring of 1993. The
   staff delivers integrated, cost-efficient primary care. Other services
          include internal medicine, nursing, orthopedics, urology,
      rehabilitation medicine, physical therapy, optometry, neurology,
     vascular surgery, ENT, nutrition counseling, pharmacy, and a mental
      hygiene unit with psychiatry and social work services. The clinic
     offers ample free parking. Shuttle service is available between the
                    clinic and the Jamaica Plain Campus.

                                 DIRECTIONS:
   From Rt. 495, Route 3 or Downtown Lowell, take the Lowell Connector to
   Plain St. (Exit 4). Take a right onto Plain St., and go across a bridge
      over railroad tracks. Take the fourth right after the bridge onto
    Cunningham St., which ends at Marshall Rd. Follow VA sign at foot of
                           the hill to VA Clinic.
